The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Murali off to Australia for surgery
 Murali will be operated on by Dr David Young Colombo: Muttiah Muralidharan flew to Australia on Thursday night for shoulder surgery. The world record-holder for most Test wickets (532 in 91 matches), pulled out of the second and final Test against South Africa on Wednesday because of intense pain in his bowling shoulder. He is also expected to miss the ODI series that begins next week. We spoke to Dr David Young (Sri Lankas Melbourne-based surgeon) last night (Wednesday) and he (Muralidharan) left tonight (Thursday), team manager Ajit Jayasekera said. According to team physio C.J. Clarke, Muralidharan is suffering from general wear and tear, and a build-up of fluid around a nerve. Sri Lankas medical team is hopeful he will be fit for next months ICC Champions Trophy in England. (Reuters)  Copyright 
